text: I like path of discovery a lot.
Just in general
I like that I can put more lands into my hand to pitch to Lord WG or put some something else I don't need into the yard.

I’ve liked it so far in testing. Dropping Avenger or a Wurm Harvest chews through a lot of the deck.
I like Explore as a mechanic a lot
That’s dumb
Ew
I’m not running Wurm Harvest in my initial build just because it’s fairly mana intensive for a bunch of 1/1s that I currently can’t buff.
Path is a card that feels slept on, and in a year or three people will be talking about it way more
I have a bit of sacrifice in my build at the moment. I need to figure out what to cut to include buffs
i'm using path in vaevictis

Explore as a mechanic plays a lot better than it looks too. I built a Slimefoot Brawl deck, and flipping over a nonland for a token and making 5 saprolings into 2/2s is good. Then you bin the top card at the end of the chain
